After Windows update KB5007186, source tree stopped launching. The splashscreen was shown but the app was never openned nor listed in the task manager.

Tried running directly from C:\Users\<username>\AppData\Local\SourceTree\app-3.4.6\SourceTree.exe but the result was the same: splashscreen was shown but the app was never openned nor listed in the task manager.

Also tried reinstalling SourceTree (SourceTreeSetup-3.4.6.exe) but the same was happening to the installer: the splashcreen was shown but the installer was never openned.

Uninstalled the app from the Control Panel (Programs and Features), and tried to install again. Same result: splashcreen was shown but the installer was never openned.

Removed the SourceTree and Atlassian folders from C:\Users\<username>\AppData\Local and tried to install again. The same happened, splashcreen was shown but the installer was never openned. But... going back to the C:\Users\<username>\AppData\Local folder I saw that the SourceTree folder was created again, with all files inside, including SourceTree.exe.

So I tried to run directly again from C:\Users\<username>\AppData\Local\SourceTree\app-3.4.6\SourceTree.exe. Same result as above.

Then I found out that there is a folder with some logs: C:\Users\<username>\AppData\Local\SquirrelTemp.

